Because \(G_{:,j}\neq\overline{G}_{:,j}\), then there exists a \(k\) (\(k<d\)), such that \(g_{kj}\neq\overline{g}_{kj}\) and \(g_{ij}=\overline{g}_{ij}(i>k)\). We have

\[\left|\delta^{-k+1}(g_{kj}-\overline{g}_{kj})\right|\geq\delta^{-k+2}.\]

However,

